hkcircle                              macro                             hkcircle

NAME
     hhkkcciirrccllee - scan along an arc in the HHKK-plane in reciprocal space

SYNOPSIS

     hhkkcciirrccllee rraaddiiuuss aannggllee__ssttaarrtt aannggllee__eenndd iinntteerrvvaallss ttiimmee [[eexxpprreessssiioonn]]

DESCRIPTION

     The hhkkcciirrccllee macro scans along a circular arc in the HHKK-plane in reciprocal
     space.  The radius of the arc is given by rraaddiiuuss and the arc runs from
     aannggllee__ssttaarrtt to aannggllee__eenndd.  The number of data points collected will be
     iinntteerrvvaallss++11.

     Count time is given by ttiimmee, which if positive, specifies seconds and if
     negative, specifies monitor counts.

     The optional last argument can supply expressions to be evaluated after HH
     and KK are calculated for each point.  You may, for example, supply an
     expression to calculate values for LL or include expressions to offset the
     values of HH and KK.

EXAMPLES

     hhkkcciirrccllee 11 00 9900 1100 6600 ""HH ++== ..55;; KK ++== ..55""
     hhkkcciirrccllee 11 00 9900 1100 6600 LL==HH//..112255
     hhkkcciirrccllee 11 00 336600 1100 6600 LL==00

